args: Oh, Elisanne and Alex!\nCome in and take a load off.
So this is the cafe I've heard about.
It's the perfect seaside hideaway. Cold\ndrinks and scrumptious snacks abound.
I'll take your word on that. We might have\nanother problem on our hands, though...
Hey, that woman there... Is that...?
Yeah, the special winner of the contest.
My apologies. I suppose it was foolish to\nhope we'd escape notice someplace this\npopulated.
My kingdom for a place we can relax\nwithout a million eyes on us. *sigh*
I'd heard the rumors, but wow. You really\nare the name on everyone's lips, Alex.
I bet if you were to be our barker,\nwe could DOUBLE our sales!
Excuse you! What am I, chopped liver?
Huh? No, that's not what I—
I can't believe this! I have my pride!\nAre you forgetting who worked her tail\noff last summer to help this place thrive?
You know what? Let's make a little game\nout of this, Alex. You and I will compete\nto prove which of us makes a better barker!
Two ladies stand before me, but only ONE\ncan take home the title of the Best Barker\nin the Business!
Oho ho ho! My business senses are telling\nme we're sitting on a gold mine here!\nAlex, will you rise to Amane's challenge?
You're on board with this too?!
There's something in it for you, naturally.\nIf you win, I'll let you borrow my villa.
And said villa comes with a private beach!\nWe're talking 24-hour access to surf and\nturf without any pesky rubberneckers!
Are you sure, Alex? This sounds like a\nsurefire way to attract even more attention.
You're not wrong... But I'm ready for it.
I came to the beach specifically so you\nand I could have a vacation together.
I can conquer this particular mountain if\nit means you and I actually get to do that!
The rules are simple: whoever brings in\nmore customers within the time limit wins\nthe title of Best Barker in the Business!
(I'll need to devise a strategy here...)
Well, if it isn't our winner, Alex!\nWhat are you up to?
Hello. I remember you from the contest.\nI'm, er, working as a barker for the cafe\nover there for...reasons.
Well, fancy that. Sounds like I'd better\ndrop by!
You serious?! Alex is working at that cafe?\nI don't need much more convincing than\nthat to check it out!
That's fame for ya. She's bringing folks in\nby the boatload just by standing here.
Now, let's have a look at her competition...
Aha, you're here! This way, everyone!
Hee hee hee. All my dragon buds turned\nout for me!
Good hustle, Amane, but I'm afraid it's not\nvalid if you just call in friends as a favor.
You need to attract customers like\na proper barker would.
I'm well aware of that. My plan doesn't\nend there. Look closely!
Welcome, welcome, one and all!\nCome on down and dine with DRAGONS\nwhile you beat the summer heat!
Whoa, Siren's there? You're tellin' me I\ncould kick back while gazing at that\nbeautiful idol dragon?! That RULES!
Look how cute that round white dragon is!\nI wanna eat here, big sis!
Well, would you look at that?\nOkay. Let's check it out.
A bold strategy! No complaints from me,\nthen. Lots of points for you, Amane!
You see that, Alex? That's what\nEXPERIENCE in this biz gets you!
I'm going to lose at this rate...\nI need a new plan of attack, and fast!
Let me give you some insider advice, Alex.
The key to turning things around is ADDED\nVALUE. You know, fanservice with a smile!
Entertain the customers who come to visit.\nWord of mouth will get around, and even\nmore folks will start showing just for you!
I follow the logic, but, er... I don't exactly\nhave the sunniest disposition, you know?
...Actually, wait. This is no time to hem\nand haw. Nothing to it but to do it.
I swore I'd get through this, so I could\nspend my vacation with Elisanne!
That's the spirit, Alex! Knock 'em dead\nout there! Just...not so dead they can't\nreach their wallets.
Close one there. I managed to catch it\nbefore it hit the ground.
Whoa, you are FAST! Thank you.
I'm just glad I could help.
Do take your time and enjoy your meal.
*sigh* Entertaining people like this\nis hard. Did I smile right...?
You were PERFECT, Alex. Take a look at\nwhat your customers are out there saying!

Get this, people: Alex served me here at
this cafe, and she knocked my socks off!
Which is crazy, because I'm wearing
sandals!
She has this whole stoic-meets-stylish\nvibe going, but she also gave me a shy\nsmile! The girl's multitalented as heck!
Seriously? I have GOT to get in on that.\n'Scuse me, pardon me, coming through!
Welcome, WELCOME! Table for one?\nRight this way!
Well, that seems good.\nI'll keep this up, then!
Well done today, both of you.\nYou had crowds coming in droves!
Now, to announce the winner of our little\ncontest for Best Barker in the Business...
I've tallied the number of customers\nyou each brought in, and survey says...\nit's a draw!
A draw? But then what happens with the\nvilla you said you'd let me borrow?
Yes, well, the condition was whether\nor not you WON in the competition...
But both of you did splendid work—so\nmuch that I couldn't possibly say which\nof you is better as a barker.
And as such, today, you're BOTH winners!
Yep, that checks out.\nI run this joint, after all!
But you gave some seriously wonderful\nservice to those customers, Alex.\nI'm more than okay with this outcome!
Amane's right. You worked really hard,\nAlex, so as promised, my villa is yours!
Really? I truly owe you, Nina!
Finally, we can get this trip back on track!
